The paper focuses on innovations in annotation methodology for Reading Comprehension (RC) datasets and models, which is a common topic in the Natural Language Processing (NLP) field. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of AI models in the annotation process, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper explores the reproducibility and generalization of the adversarial effect, which could be relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
